## Getting Started

```bash
# Start PostgreSQL
docker compose up -d

# Install dependencies
bun install

# Push database schema
bun run db:push

# Start development server
bun run dev:web
```

## Scripts

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `bun run dev` | Start all apps in parallel |
| `bun run dev:web` | Start web app only |
{%- if include_mobile %}
| `bun run dev:mobile` | Start Expo dev server |
{%- endif %}
{%- if include_desktop %}
| `bun run dev:desktop` | Start Tauri desktop app |
{%- endif %}
{%- if include_storybook %}
| `bun run dev:storybook` | Start Storybook |
{%- endif %}
| `bun run build` | Production build |
| `bun run type-check` | TypeScript type checking |
| `bun run lint` | Run linter |
| `bun run test` | Run tests |
| `bun run db:push` | Push schema to database |
| `bun run db:studio` | Open Drizzle Studio |
| `bun run db:generate` | Generate migration |
| `bun run db:migrate` | Run migrations |

## Architecture

```
{{ project_name }}/
├── apps/
│   ├── web/           # Next.js web application
{%- if include_mobile %}
│   ├── mobile/        # Expo mobile app
{%- endif %}
{%- if include_desktop %}
│   └── desktop/       # Tauri desktop app
{%- endif %}
├── packages/
│   ├── api/           # Server-side logic (auth, payments)
│   ├── db/            # Database schemas and client
│   ├── types/         # Shared TypeScript types
│   ├── ui/            # Shared UI utilities
│   └── modules/       # Feature modules (Zustand stores)
└── docker-compose.yml
```

## Environment

Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and fill in the values:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
